casebody.data:
Thursday, December 14, 1995

MERIT DOCKET

95-1997. State ex rel. Rossman v. Cleveland.

In Mandamus. On motion to dismiss. Motion to dismiss sustained. Cause dismissed.

On motion for attorney fees. Sua sponte, relators are ordered to submit bill, documentation, and brief in support of their application for attorney fees, to which respondent may respond.

F.E. Sweeney, J., dissents and would grant the motion for attorney fees. Moyer, C.J., and Pfeifer, J., dissent and would deny the motion for attorney fees.
